NNAAMMEE
       hnb - Hierarchical notebook

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       hhnnbb [_f_i_l_e] [_o_p_t_i_o_n_s]
       [_c_o_m_m_a_n_d [_c_o_m_m_a_n_d] .. ]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This manual page documents briefly the hhnnbb
       hierarchical notebook.

       hhnnbb  is an ncurses program to organize many
       kinds of data in one place, for example addresses,
       todo lists, ideas,  book  reviews  or  to  store
       snippets of brainstorming, to make a structured packing
       list or just to take random notes.  It can export
       ascii/html/latex/postscript, supports todo checkboxes,
       checkbox trees with percentages and searching.

       hhnnbb  uses  a simple ascii file for storing
       your notes. This file can be specified on the command
       line. If not specified, ~/.hnb is  loaded  (or created
       if missing).

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       hhnnbb can be invoked with the following options:

       --hh,, ----hheellpp
              Show summary of options.

       --vv,, ----vveerrssiioonn
              Show version of program.

       --tt,, ----ttuuttoorriiaall
              Load the tutorial instead of a database.

       --rrcc <<_f_i_l_e>>
              Load an other config file than default.

       --uuii <<ccuurrsseess||ccllii>>
              Specify user interface to use.

       --ee     Run  commands  in noninteractive mode
       (start hnb with the cli ui
              and type `help' to get more information).

FFIILLEESS
       ~/.hnb The default file for your notes. To use an
       other,  specify  its
              name on the command line.


       ~/.hnbrc
              The  default  configuration  file.  To load
              an other config file than default, use the
              --rrcc command-line option.


SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       For more information on the usage of the program,
       load the tutorial  or press FF11 in the program.

       hnb homepage: http://hnb.sourceforge.net

AAUUTTHHOORR
